<h1>Online Bible: New World Translation of the Holy Scriptures</h1>
</noscript>
<p class="title">Jeremiah 45:1-5</p>
<form class="formtext">
<input type="hidden" name="chapterCount" value="52">
<input type="hidden" name="verseCount" value="5">
<p><a name="bk1" class="vsAnchor">1</a>
       <span id="vs1">The word that Jeremiah the prophet spoke to Bar&acute;uch the son of Ne&middot;ri&acute;ah when he wrote in a book these words from the mouth of Jeremiah in the fourth year of Je&middot;hoi&acute;a&middot;kim the son of Jo&middot;si&acute;ah, the king of Judah, saying:</span>
</p>

<p><a name="bk2" class="vsAnchor">2</a>
       <span id="vs2">“This is what Jehovah the God of Israel has said concerning you, O Bar&acute;uch,</span> <a name="bk3" class="vsAnchor">3</a>
       <span id="vs3">‘You have said: “Woe, now, to me, for Jehovah has added grief to my pain! I have grown weary because of my sighing, and no resting-place have I found.”’</span>
</p>

<p><a name="bk4" class="vsAnchor">4</a>
       <span id="vs4">“This is what you should say to him, ‘This is what Jehovah has said: “Look! What I have built up I am tearing down, and what I have planted I am uprooting, even all the land itself.</span> <a name="bk5" class="vsAnchor">5</a>
       <span id="vs5">But as for you, you keep seeking great things for yourself. Do not keep on seeking.”’</span>
</p>

<p> 
       <span id="vs5-2">“‘For here I am bringing in a calamity upon all flesh,’ is the utterance of Jehovah, ‘and I will give you your soul as a spoil in all the places to which you may go.’”</span>
</p>
</form>

